      "markdown": "# What is a digital image?\n\nMathematical definition of color image:\n\nA 2D (color)digital image is a 2D function defined on a 2D domain (usually rectangular domain):\n\n$$f:=(f_{R},f_{G},f_{B}):\\Omega\\to\\mathbb{R}^{3}$$\n\n$f_{R},f_{G},f_{B}$ are the intensity/brightness/grey level corresponding gtoR,G and B respectively \n\n\n\nCombination of R, G, B forms the full LS spectrum of color!\n\nWE WILLF FOcUS ON: Grayscale image!",
